                <note type="abstract">Includes an edition, based on a single Ms. in the British Library, of Yaʿqūb al-Qirqisānī’s Kitāb al-anwār wa-ʾl-marāqib, part 5, chap. 35 (pp. 453–56), which offers testimony to the existence in the early-10th century of a (likely Qaraite) translation of the Pentateuch. This testimony is expressly noted, and an English translation of the entire chapter supplied, by H. Ben-Shammai in his contribution to the 1982 Nemoy Festschrift {https://www.zotero.org/groups/538215/biblia_arabica/items/itemKey/F86KGYXS/q/ben-shammai}.</note>
